Popular datasets refer to those with a high number of accesses, including both views and downloads; 
A dataset's total views and downloads are considered as a measure of its popularity, with the threshold set at 50;
For a dataset to be considered popular, it must have exceeded this threshold of 50 total views and downloads.

; A high number of unique users may indicate the dataset's popularity or relevance in the research community; 
; Average access duration may reflect the complexity or depth of the dataset, with longer durations suggesting more comprehensive or detailed data; 
; The number of papers and total citations associated with a dataset can indicate its impact or influence within the research field.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(link_id) AS total_links
FROM dataset_paper_links
WHERE description LIKE '%used in the research paper%';
